    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, sorry—I'm the procurement manager here at Apex. I just got that message from the steel vendor. They're claiming they can only hold the current price for 24 hours because of high demand and low stock. \n\nWhat's your recommendation? Do we need to panic and lock this in right now to avoid a shortage, or is there a way we can use this situation to push for a better rate? Give me a strategy.",
